<item>
            <title>[LU-7276] llog_reader doesn&apos;t process CM_SKIP records like the kernel</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7276</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;llog_reader&lt;/tt&gt; command doesn&apos;t process the &lt;tt&gt;CM_SKIP&lt;/tt&gt; records in config log &lt;tt&gt;LCFG_MARKER&lt;/tt&gt; records same manner that the kernel does, which can result in misleading output in some cases.  In particular, llog_reader will report &lt;tt&gt;SKIP&lt;/tt&gt; for all records between &lt;tt&gt;CM_START|CM_SKIP&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;CM_END|CM_SKIP&lt;/tt&gt;, but the kernel stops skipping records at the first CM_END record regardless of whether or not there is a CM_SKIP there, and definitely not into the subsequent configuration stanzas.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="32576">LU-7276</key>
